Every world is full of contradictions.[l][r]
[r]The lament of the many creatures that have been unjustly exterminated. [l][r]
Innocent people hanged simply to satisfy the vanity of those in power.[l][r]
Towns and villages burned for no reason.[l][r]
There are people who take their own lives on the same day they laugh happily.[l][r]
[r] Before my memories of the "other world" returned, I couldn't help but wonder about it. The cruel stories of the real world don't flow as smoothly as the stories in the book. [l][r]
The world is not right. But the cold reality is that it is true. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="news.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
These tragedies, shining like the starry sky, are sensationally told in train advertisements, in the margins of newspapers, on variety shows, and on online news. [l][r]
People who are fascinated by it. They are indifferent and just look at it from the outside like a story in a book because it doesn't really concern them. But that's wrong, it's true. [l][r]
The world revolves around contradictions. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="lastroot.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]I don't feel that this is a contradiction now.[l][r]
We lived in a world just for the two of us, and although it was painful, it was fun. That world cruelly taught me everything. [l][r]
[r]The world has been in contradiction and despair since the beginning. [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

