Even in the ruins of a city where you can't find anything no matter how hard you search, in the middle of a white snowstorm, [l]even in the pitch black darkness, Chi-chan looked straight ahead, looked up, and took me there. [l][r]
If you despair of the world and just enjoy yourself, then what happens afterwards doesn't matter.
But, to me, who had always pretended to be strong while hiding the trembling deep inside my heart, it was [l]the truth is... [r]
It was Chi-chan. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="lastwall.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]...Maybe he didn't notice. Maybe he'd already forgotten. [l][r]

Right now, Chi-chan seems to be constantly looking down. [r]
He desperately knows that something he's lost isn't there, but he just keeps crouching down and looks like he can't walk. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

