It doesn't belong to anyone. I know it's not mine. [l][r]
But I can't let go. I'm scared to open my hand, to look outside.
I feel like a little child clinging to his mother on an unfamiliar train. I am clinging to you with fear and love, unable to let go. [l][r]
[r]Yesterday or today, Yu was looking out the window. When I asked her if she was worried about what was going on outside, she shook her head. [l][r]
Yu closed the curtains, looked at me, and laughed, saying it was nothing. The flat light of the ceiling light made Yu's doll-like hair shine. [l][r]
I thought it was beautiful. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
